Chicago Bull's point guard and reigning MVP Derrick Rose debuted a new adidas adiZero Rose 2.5 colorway in their match-up with the Philadelphia 76ers on St. Patrick's Day, one of the most celebrated holidays in the Chicago area. Decked out in Kelly Green, the shoe hooks up to the Bulls' special green uniforms, which they've worn each season since the NBA's inaugural St. Patrick's Day celebration in 2006.

Nike scrapped the anticipated release of these shoes after the Cavaliers were eliminated by Orlando, and King James failed to reach it to the finals where he would have faced Kobe Bryant's Lakers. The Lakers went on to Victory that year while Nike liquidated the very few pairs of this shoe produced ahead of time in anticipation that LeBron would finally face Kobe on the big stage in 2009 NBA finals. These shoes are extremely difficult to come by and only a handful of collectors have ever seen these in person..
